headlines.description: — Myles Turner had 32 points and 10 rebounds, Caris LeVert had 24 points and 11 assists, and the Indiana Pacers beat the Houston Rockets 118-106 Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Turner, LeVert lead short-handed Pacers over Rockets 118-106

events.name: New Orleans Pelicans at Orlando Magic

headlines.description: — Brandon Ingram scored 31 points, Josh Hart hit two clutch 3-pointers in the second half to thwart an Orlando rally, and the New Orleans Pelicans beat the Magic 110-104 on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Ingram, Hart lead Pelicans past Magic for 4th straight win

headlines.description: — Kevin Huerter sat in the parking lot when he found out he flunked a COVID-19 test. Sharife Cooper was escorted out of Atlanta's locker room once his results came back.
headlines.shortLinkText: Hawks beat 76ers 98-96; Embiid misses at the buzzer

headlines.description: — Tyler Herro scored 29 points, Max Strus added 26 and the Miami Heat rallied to beat the short-handed Detroit Pistons 115-112 on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Herro, Strus power Heat to 115-112 comeback win over Pistons

events.name: Washington Wizards at New York Knicks

headlines.description: — Washington’s Kyle Kuzma had Kemba Walker’s recent stellar numbers in the back of his mind and wondered why the New York guard had been buried at the end of the bench for nearly three weeks.
headlines.shortLinkText: Wizards withstand Walker's big night, beat Knicks 124-117

headlines.description: — Khris Middleton and the Milwaukee Bucks have won more than they've lost in five games with Giannis Antetokounmpo in the COVID-19 protocols, thanks to two wins in Texas on a back-to-back.
headlines.shortLinkText: Middleton, Bucks top Mavs 102-95 with pair of superstars out

headlines.description: — Kelly Oubre Jr., P.J. Washington and the Charlotte reserves helped recapture the momentum with their early fourth-quarter spurt.
headlines.shortLinkText: Washington, Oubre help Hornets rally past Nuggets, 115-107

events.name: Oklahoma City Thunder at Phoenix Suns

headlines.description: — Cam Johnson played some of the best basketball of his three-year career when All-Star teammate Devin Booker was out with a hamstring injury.
headlines.shortLinkText: NBA-leading Suns win 5th straight, beating Thunder 113-101

headlines.description: — Donovan Mitchell scored 28 points and the Utah Jazz beat the short-handed Minnesota Timberwolves 128-116 on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Mitchell scores 28, Jazz ease past Timberwolves 128-116

events.name: Memphis Grizzlies at Golden State Warriors

headlines.description: — Stephen Curry scored 46 points and made eight 3-pointers, Gary Payton Jr. added a clutch 3-pointer late in the fourth quarter and the Golden State Warriors held off the Memphs Grizzlies 113-104 on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Curry scores 46, Warriors hold off pesky Grizzlies 113-104

events.name: Brooklyn Nets at Portland Trail Blazers
San Antonio Spurs at Los Angeles Lakers

headlines.description: — Keita Bates-Diop scored a career-high 30 points while making all 11 of his shots, and the San Antonio Spurs routed the slumping Los Angeles Lakers 138-110 on Thursday night in the final event at Staples Center under the 22-year-old arena's original...
headlines.shortLinkText: Spurs rout depleted Lakers 138-110 in last Staples game
